he Army Commendation Medal  The Joint Service Achievement Medal  The Army Achievement Medal  the Army Good Conduct medal  The Armed Forces Expeditionary Medal  The Humanitarian Service Medal  The Southwest Asian Service Medal  The Army Service Ribbon  The Overseas Service Ribbon  German Parachute Wings  Canadian Parachute Wings  British Parachute Wings  The Expert Infantry Badge  The Combat Infantry Badge  and The Master Parachutist Badge  He joined the Commandant s Staff in September 2001  and is an Honorary Brother Rat to the Class of 2004  His duties involve the Appearance and Discipline of the Corps of Cadets  Parades  Color Guard activities  Barracks Maintenance and Appearance  and Supervision of the New Cadet Military Training program  Sergeant Major Neel is married to the former Kimberly Ann Dennis of Birmingham Alabama  Their son  Jonathon Neel  a veteran of the War in Iraq and graduate of the University of Maryland University College  is the Information Security Officer at the UVA School of Medicine  Their daughter  Capt  Elise Neel  a graduate Mary Baldwin College  has recently returned from serving with the 82nd Airborne Division in Afghanistan and is currently assigned to Ft  Eustis Virginia  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives