ackson Arch  Barracks Lexington  VA 24450 Sergeant Major John Neel  Sergeant Major to the Corps of Cadets Sergeant Major Neel hails from Birmingham Alabama  He joined the Army in 1976  and was trained as a Parachute Infantryman  His first assignment was with the 505th Parachute Infantry Regiment  82d Airborne Division  Ft Bragg NC  Sergeant Major Neel served over 15 years with the 505th as Rifleman  Driver  Armorer  Team Leader  Squad Leader  Scout Section Leader  Rifle Platoon Sergeant  Scout Platoon Sergeant  Operations Sergeant  and 1st Sergeant  Sergeant Major Neel has served three tours with NATO in Izmir Turkey as an Operations Sergeant  and most recently as the Senior Enlisted Advisor and Sergeant Major for Joint Command Southeast  He served for two years on Her Majesty s service as 8th Platoon Sergeant  1st Battalion  of the British Parachute Regiment  He is a graduate of Class 47 United States Army Sergeants Major Academy  FT Bliss TX and served as the Sergeant Major of the Army ROTC Department  Virginia Military Institute from July 1997  July 2000  Sergeant Major Neel s deployments include Grenada in 1983  Joint Task Force 6 along the New Mexico   Mexico border in 1992  Operation Harvest Bear in Panama to quell the riots in the Cuban refugee camps in 1995  and to Kosovo as the Operations Sergeant  J3  HQ KFOR 4 in September 2000  Sergeant Major Neel s awards and decorations include  The Legion of Merit  The Bronze Star  The Defense Meritorious Service Medal  The Army Meritorious Service Medal  The Joint Service Commendation Medal  The Army Commendation Medal  The Joint Service Achievement Medal  The Army Achievement Medal  the Army Good Conduct medal  The Armed Forces Expeditionary Medal  The Humanitarian Service Medal  The Southwest Asian Service Medal  The Army Service Ribbon  The Overseas Service Ribbon  German Parachute Wings  Canadian Parachute Wings  British Parachute Wings  The Expert Infantry Badge  The Combat Infantry Badge  and The Master Parachutist Badge  He joined the Commandant s Staff in September 2001  and is an Honorary Brother Rat to the Class of 2004  His duties involve the Appearance and Discipline of the Corps of Cadets  Parades  Color Guard activities  Barracks Maintenance and Appearance  and Supervision of the New Cadet Military Training program  Sergeant Major Neel is married to the former Kimberly Ann Dennis of Birmingham Alabama  Their son  Jonathon Neel  a veteran of the War in Iraq and graduate of the University of Maryland University College  is the Information Security Officer at the UVA School of Medicine  Their daughter  Capt  Elise Neel  a graduate Mary Baldwin College  has recently returned from serving with the 82nd Airborne Division in Afghanistan and is currently assigned to Ft  Eustis Virginia Commandant s Office Clubs and Events Health  Welfare  and Safety Regimental Band About Cadet Leadership Student Consumer Information Parents and Family Info Cadet Sign In   Out Cadet in Barracks   Cadet out of Barracks   Holly Leech  Commandant Office Manager P   540  464 7313 F 540  464 7748 E  leechhc vmi edu   OC  540 464 7293  OB 135  Evening Night OC 540 464 7962  OB 123  or 540 464 7285   NB 496  Guard Room  540 464 7294  Jackson Arch  Commandant s Office Virginia Military Institute Jackson Arch  Barracks Lexington  VA 24450  Commandant s Office Clubs and Events Health  Welfare  and Safety Regimental Band About Cadet Leadership Student Consumer Information Parents and Family Info Cadet Sign In   Out Cadet in Barracks   Cadet out of Barracks   Holly Leech  Commandant Office Manager P   540  464 7313 F 540  464 7748 E  leechhc vmi edu   OC  540 464 7293  OB 135  Evening Night OC 540 464 7962  OB 123  or 540 464 7285   NB 496  Guard Room  540 464 7294  Jackson Arch  Commandant s Office Virginia Military Institute Jackson Arch  Barracks Lexington  VA 24450 Commandant s Office Clubs and Events Health  Welfare  and Safety Regimental Band About Cadet Leadership Student Consumer Information Parents and Family Info Commandant s Office Commandant s Office Clubs and Events Clubs and Events Health  Welfare  and Safety Health  Welfare  and Safety Regimental Band Regimental Band About Cadet Leadership About Cadet Leadership Student Consumer Information Student Consumer Information Parents and Family Info Parents and Family Info Cadet Sign In   Out Cadet in Barracks   Cadet out of Barracks   Holly Leech  Commandant Office Manager P   540  464 7313 F 540  464 7748 E  leechhc vmi edu   OC  540 464 7293  OB 135  Evening Night OC 540 464 7962  OB 123  or 540 464 7285   NB 496  Guard Room  540 464 7294  Jackson Arch  Commandant s Office Virginia Military Institute Jackson Arch  Barracks Lexington  VA 24450 Cadet Sign In   Out Cadet in Barracks   Cadet out of Barracks Cadet Sign In   Out Cadet Sign In   Out  Cadet in Barracks   Cadet out of Barracks Cadet in Barracks   Cadet out of Barracks Cadet in Barracks Cadet in Barracks Cadet out of Barracks Cadet out of Barracks Holly Leech  Commandant Office Manager P   540  464 7313 F 540  464 7748 E  leechhc vmi edu Holly Leech      leechhc vmi edu   OC  540 464 7293  OB 135  Evening Night OC 540 464 7962  OB 123  or 540 464 7285   NB 496  Guard Room  540 464 7294  Jackson Arch  Commandant s Office Virginia Military Institute Jackson Arch  Barracks Lexington  VA 24450        Sergeant Major John Neel  Sergeant Major to the Corps of Cadets Sergeant Major Neel hails from Birmingham Alabama  He joined the Army in 1976  and was trained as a Parachute Infantryman  His first assignment was with the 505th Parachute Infantry Regiment  82d Airborne Division  Ft Bragg NC  Sergeant Major Neel served over 15 years with the 505th as Rifleman  Driver  Armorer  Team Leader  Squad Leader  Scout Section Leader  Rifle Platoon Sergeant  Scout Platoon Sergeant  Operations Sergeant  and 1st Sergeant  Sergeant Major Neel has served three tours with NATO in Izmir Turkey as an Operations Sergeant  and most recently as the Senior Enlisted Advisor and Sergeant Major for Joint Command Southeast  He served for two years on Her Majesty s service as 8th Platoon Sergeant  1st Battalion  of the British Parachute Regiment  He is a graduate of Class 47 United States Army Sergeants Major Academy  FT Bliss TX and served as the Sergeant Major of the Army ROTC Department  Virginia Military Institute from July 1997  July 2000  Sergeant Major Neel s deployments include Grenada in 1983  Joint Task Force 6 along the New Mexico   Mexico border in 1992  Operation Harvest Bear in Panama to quell the riots in the Cuban refugee camps in 1995  and to Kosovo as the Operations Sergeant  J3  HQ KFOR 4 in September 2000  Sergeant Major Neel s awards and decorations include  The Legion of Merit  The Bronze Star  The Defense Meritorious Service Medal  The Army Meritorious Service Medal  The Joint Service Commendation Medal  The Army Commendation Medal  The Joint Service Achievement Medal  The Army Achievement Medal  the Army Good Conduct medal  The Armed Forces Expeditionary Medal  The Humanitarian Service Medal  The Southwest Asian Service Medal  The Army Service Ribbon  The Overseas Service Ribbon  German Parachute Wings  Canadian Parachute Wings  British Parachute Wings  The Expert Infantry Badge  The Combat Infantry Badge  and The Master Parachutist Badge  He joined the Commandant s Staff in September 2001  and is an Honorary Brother Rat to the Class of 2004  His duties involve the Appearance and Discipline of the Corps of Cadets  Parades  Color Guard activities  Barracks Maintenance and Appearance  and Supervision of the New Cadet Military Training program  Sergeant Major Neel is married to the former Kimberly Ann Dennis of Birmingham Alabama  Their son  Jonathon Neel  a veteran of the War in Iraq and graduate of the University of Maryland University College  is the Information Security Officer at the UVA School of Medicine  Their daughter  Capt  Elise Neel  a graduate Mary Baldwin College  has recently returned from serving with the 82nd Airborne Division in Afghanistan and is currently assigned to Ft  Eustis Virginia      Sergeant Major John Neel  Sergeant Major to the Corps of Cadets Sergeant Major Neel hails from Birmingham Alabama  He joined the Army in 1976  and was trained as a Parachute Infantryman  His first assignment was with the 505th Parachute Infantry Regiment  82d Airborne Division  Ft Bragg NC  Sergeant Major Neel served over 15 years with the 505th as Rifleman  Driver  Armorer  Team Leader  Squad Leader  Scout Section Leader  Rifle Platoon Sergeant  Scout Platoon Sergeant  Operations Sergeant  and 1st Sergeant  Sergeant Major Neel has served three tours with NATO in Izmir Turkey as an Operations Sergeant  and most recently as the Senior Enlisted Advisor and Sergeant Major for Joint Command Southeast  He served for two years on Her Majesty s service as 8th Platoon Sergeant  1st Battalion  of the British Parachute Regiment  He is a graduate of Class 47 United States Army Sergeants Major Academy  FT Bliss TX and served as the Sergeant Major of the Army ROTC Department  Virginia Military Institute from July 1997  July 2000  Sergeant Major Neel s deployments include Grenada in 1983  Joint Task Force 6 along the New Mexico   Mexico border in 1992  Operation Harvest Bear in Panama to quell the riots in the Cuban refugee camps in 1995  and to Kosovo as the Operations Sergeant  J3  HQ KFOR 4 in September 2000  Sergeant Major Neel s awards and decorations include  The Legion of Merit  The Bronze Star  The Defense Meritorious Service Medal  The Army Meritorious Service Medal  The Joint Service Commendation Medal  The Army Commendation Medal  The Joint Service Achievement Medal  The Army Achievement Medal  the Army Good Conduct medal  The Armed Forces Expeditionary Medal  The Humanitarian Service Medal  The Southwest Asian Service Medal  The Army Service Ribbon  The Overseas Service Ribbon  German Parachute Wings  Canadian Parachute Wings  British Parachute Wings  The Expert Infantry Badg